text: Alois Anderlé (7 July 1869 - 18 June 1929) was an Austrian swimmer. He competed in two events at the 1900 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1869 births Category:1929 deaths Category:Austrian male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Austria Category:Swimmers at the 1900 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Vienna
